{
  "text": "Previous studies using iron oxide nanoparticles showed that the flip angle exerts an important effect on the SI of the MR images and contrast of MRA [CITATION_1] . Different studies were performed to evaluate the flip angle effect on the MRA image quality [CITATION_2] and to determine appropriate flip angle for MRA using iron oxide nanoparticles and different MRI pulse sequences [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . They reported different flip angle values as the appropriate flip angle that leads to highest MR signal intensity for MRA. Anzai et al. reported little flip angle dependence on the image quality for abdominal MRA using USPIO nanoparticles [CITATION_5] . A study carried out by Mayo-Smith et al. showed that the maximum SI in blood samples occurred at flip angles of 30º and 60º before and after administration of AMI-227, respectively [CITATION_6] . Tanimoto et al. found the optimal flip angle of 20º for the inferior vena cava before and after US-PIO injection [CITATION_7] .",
  "correct_citation": {
